    "20 LIGHTER AIR MOTORS DUE TO NEW ALLOYS Greater Efficiency Also Possible Is Verdict of Engineering Division McCOOK FIELD DISCOVERY Departure in Construction Methods Is Explained Construction of an airplane motor tighter in weight than the present types and more efficient will be made possible through developments In the use of new alloys at the air service engineering division McCook Field Dayton Ohio it was learned here to day Two outstanding features of this pew departure in motor construction are Use of a magnesium combination which saves 200 pounds in the casting of a crankcase for an ordinary W type motor and a light nickel and copper alloy which produces parts twice as strong as the material now in use and considered standard Koth these developments have great commercial possibilities and will un doubtedly be adopted extensively engineers in the material section of McCook Field believe Adaptation of the magnesium alloy Seventh and D Sts NW Savings of Plll\u00df Hfl FREE 10 to 33 y 3 ill JHIjE HI ILII IBi jtjKjsrt Dp r r ESS I a 42piece dinner set with MING mm FURNITURE STORE CREDIT cash or charge account 11 I January Clearance Sale Use Your Credit Pay"
